    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="805"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-09T10:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1928—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Department’s telegram 25, April 27, 3 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Article 11 revised pursuant to Department’s telegram 24, April 26 [<hi
                            rend="italic">12</hi>], 6 p.m., and instruction No. 676, April
                            25th.<note n="99" xml:id="d805fn99">Instruction No. 676 not
                            printed.</note>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="1122" n="994" xml:id="pg_994"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Schüller expressed finally preference for six-year term because of
                        uncertainty of date of Senate ratification. To this I assented in view of
                        paragraph three, Department’s telegram 25.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Cabinet council is taking necessary formalities and treaty will shortly be
                        signed probably this month in conformity with instruction No. 573, April 14,
                            1927.<note n="1" xml:id="d805fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washburn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
